  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date, federal contract obligations in Minnesota total $1.3B. That total comes from 21,326 awards with an average award size of $61.2K, and obligations are down 47.5% year over year. Annual history shows prior fiscal-year obligations of $2.6B in FY21, $2.4B in FY22, $2.7B in FY23, $3B in FY24, and $2.5B in FY25, before the current FY26 total of $1.3B. The Department of Defense is the largest buyer so far in FY2026 to date at $419M, followed by the Department of Agriculture at $222M and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $219M. Industry concentrations include Ammunition (except Small Arms) Manufacturing at $161M and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $124M. The largest individual vendors in FY2026 to date are NORTHROP GRUMMAN SYSTEMS CORPORATION at $160M and MCGOUGH CONSTRUCTION CO., LLC at $106M. All figures are contract obligations and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How concentrated is federal contracting in Minnesota?",
        "body": "Obligations in FY2026 to date total $1.3B across 21,326 awards, producing an average award size of $61.2K. Obligations are down 47.5% year over year, and the FY26 total follows prior fiscal-year totals of $2.5B in FY25 and $3B in FY24."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What agencies and industries are driving procurement?",
        "body": "The top buying agency in FY2026 to date is the Department of Defense with $419M, followed by the Department of Agriculture at $222M and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $219M. Leading industries include Ammunition (except Small Arms) Manufacturing at $161M and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $124M, while NORTHROP GRUMMAN SYSTEMS CORPORATION leads vendors at $160M."
      }
    ]
  },
