    {
      "q": "How much federal contract money goes to Minnesota?",
      "a": "About $1.3B in federal contract obligations have gone to Minnesota in FY2026 to date. That total is composed of 21,326 awards with an average award size of $61.2K and represents a year-over-year decline of down 47.5%."
    },
    {
      "q": "Which agencies award the most contracts in Minnesota?",
      "a": "The Department of Defense awards the most contracts in Minnesota in FY2026 to date at $419M, followed by the Department of Agriculture at $222M and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $219M. Other top buying agencies in the state include the General Services Administration at $139M and the Department of Health and Human Services at $111M."
